The paper proposes a novel 3D CNN network for hyperspectral image classification, which involves processing individual spatiospectral feature rich cubes through 3D convolutional layers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a model that incorporates residual features from multiple stages in the network, which is a common technique used in deep learning and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also conducts experiments for performance analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with processing images, which could also suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
